[Article in Portuguese]

Salviano RJ(1), de Mello RP, Beck LC, d'Almeida JM.

Author information:
(1)Departamento de Biologia, Instituto Oswaldo Cruz, Rio de Janeiro, RJ, Brasil.

Experiments with Squamatoides trivitattus were carried out in two different 
controlled temperatures (16 +/- 1 degree C/50-60% RH and 27 +/- 1 degree 
C/70-80% RH). The viability of larvae and pupae at 27 degrees C was 89.82% and 
