weeks for males and 2.42 for females. At 27 degrees C a life-expectancy of 1.15 
weeks for males and 0.78 week for females was recorded. The average life-spans 
for males and females at 16 degrees C were 3.5 +/- 2.0 and 3.8 +/- 2.6 weeks, 
respectively, and 1.9 +/- 1.2 weeks for both sexes. At 27 degrees C, the 
longevity recorded was of 2.1 +/- 1.3 weeks for males and 1.7 +/- 1.1 week for 
females.

