Measuring contraceptive effectiveness: a conceptual framework.

Steiner M(1), Dominik R, Trussell J, Hertz-Picciott I.

Author information:
(1)Family Health International, Research Triangle Park, North Carolina, USA.

Comment in
    Obstet Gynecol. 1997 Jan;89(1):157-8.

We present a conceptual model that outlines the four measures of how well a 
contraceptive method works: 1) efficacy, 2) effectiveness, 3) perfect-use 
pregnancy rate, and 4) typical-use pregnancy rate. Moreover, we illustrate how 
four variables influence these measures: 1) capacity to conceive, 2) frequency 
